      <h2>6. Location Services</h2>
      <p>ParkArmor requests "When In Use" location access from iOS to record your parking coordinate when you save a spot. Location data is stored exclusively in local device storage and is never transmitted to any server or third party.</p>
      <p><strong>Location accuracy disclaimer:</strong> GPS accuracy depends on your device hardware, environmental conditions (tunnels, garages, urban canyons), and iOS location services. ParkArmor provides the GPS coordinate as reported by your device and makes no guarantee of precision. You are responsible for confirming your actual parking location.</p>
      <p>ParkArmor does not request background location access and does not track your location while you are away from the App.</p>

      <h2>7. Notifications</h2>
      <p>The parking timer feature uses iOS local notifications (UNUserNotificationCenter). All notifications are scheduled and delivered on-device. No push notification server is used. Notification permission is optional &mdash; the timer will run without it, but you will not receive on-screen alerts. You may revoke notification permission at any time in iOS Settings.</p>

